I’ve a feeling in my water about corona. No, not the beer, but the dreaded Covid-19. The accuracy of the feeling is yet to be proved, but together with my water, of which I have plenty, given my age, normally comes reasonably close. The same can be said of conspiracy theories, but I detest the phrase, because it’s usually used for arcane reasons. Whereas a feeling has no mission and is without bias. We are told that the coronavirus had its source in a market where slaughtered bats and other animals are sold as delicacies. The bat, in particular, carries...